.NET Framework 3.5.name: OVRCameraRig
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: A head-tracked stereoscopic virtual reality camera rig.

fields.name: useFixedUpdateForTracking
fields.summary: If true, all tracked anchors are updated in FixedUpdate instead of Update to favor physics fidelity. \note: If the fixed update rate doesn't match the rendering framerate (OVRManager.display.appFramerate), the anchors will visibly judder.

fields.name: usePerEyeCameras
fields.summary: If true, separate cameras will be used for the left and right eyes.

methods.linkedSyntax: private Transform ConfigureEyeAnchor(Transform root, XRNode eye)

events.name: UpdatedAnchors
events.summary: Occurs when the eye pose anchors have been set.

properties.name: centerEyeAnchor
properties.summary: Always coincides with average of the left and right eye poses.

properties.name: leftEyeAnchor
properties.summary: Always coincides with the pose of the left eye.

properties.name: leftHandAnchor
properties.summary: Always coincides with the pose of the left hand.

properties.name: rightEyeAnchor
properties.summary: Always coincides with the pose of the right eye.

properties.name: rightHandAnchor
properties.summary: Always coincides with the pose of the right hand.

properties.name: trackerAnchor
properties.summary: Always coincides with the pose of the sensor.

properties.name: trackingSpace
properties.summary: Provides a root transform for all anchors in tracking space.
